The paper deals with the problem of achieving the maximum coding rate over a communication channel, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT). The use of variable-length stop-feedback codes is a specific coding scheme that is being investigated, which falls under the category of coding theory and its applications (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the point-to-point case, which involves the transmission of information between two nodes, and thus falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.SI). The authors use mathematical analysis to derive their results, which involves the use of probability theory and statistics, and thus falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the asymptotic behavior of the maximum coding rate, which is a topic of interest in machine learning and statistical analysis (cs.LG).
